## 3. CTEs (Common Table Expressions)

### 3.1 Basic / stacking CTEs for readable pipelines
```sql
WITH cleaned AS (
    SELECT * FROM raw_orders WHERE amount > 0
),
enriched AS (
    SELECT c.*, cust.country
    FROM cleaned c
    JOIN customers cust ON cust.id = c.customer_id
)
SELECT country, SUM(amount) AS total
FROM enriched
GROUP BY country;
```

### 3.2 Recursive CTE (org charts, bill-of-materials, date spines)
```sql
-- Org chart: all reports under a given manager
WITH RECURSIVE org_chart AS (
    SELECT id, name, manager_id, 1 AS level
    FROM employees
    WHERE id = 1  -- the root/CEO

    UNION ALL

    SELECT e.id, e.name, e.manager_id, oc.level + 1
    FROM employees e
    JOIN org_chart oc ON e.manager_id = oc.id
)
SELECT * FROM org_chart ORDER BY level;
```

```sql
-- Generate a date spine (extremely common DE utility pattern)
WITH RECURSIVE dates AS (
    SELECT DATE '2026-01-01' AS d
    UNION ALL
    SELECT d + INTERVAL '1 day' FROM dates WHERE d < DATE '2026-12-31'
)
SELECT d FROM dates;
```
BigQuery: use `GENERATE_DATE_ARRAY()` instead of a recursive CTE — much cheaper.

