## 7. JSON / semi-structured data (very relevant — most Dutch stacks ingest JSON events)

### PostgreSQL
```sql
SELECT
    payload->>'event_type' AS event_type,
    (payload->'user'->>'id')::int AS user_id,
    payload #>> '{metadata,source}' AS source
FROM events;

-- Expand a JSON array into rows
SELECT event_id, item
FROM events, jsonb_array_elements(payload->'items') AS item;
```

### BigQuery
```sql
SELECT
    JSON_VALUE(payload, '$.event_type') AS event_type,
    JSON_VALUE(payload, '$.user.id') AS user_id
FROM events;
```

### Snowflake
```sql
SELECT
    payload:event_type::string AS event_type,
    payload:user.id::int AS user_id
FROM events;
```

