## 8. Date/Time handling & time zones

Netherlands sits in CET/CEST — DST transitions are a real, recurring bug source in pipelines.

```sql
-- Convert UTC storage time to Amsterdam local time (handles DST automatically)
SELECT
    event_time_utc,
    event_time_utc AT TIME ZONE 'UTC' AT TIME ZONE 'Europe/Amsterdam' AS event_time_local
FROM events;

-- Truncate to week/month for aggregation
SELECT DATE_TRUNC('week', order_date) AS week_start, SUM(amount)
FROM orders
GROUP BY 1;

-- Generate a full calendar of dates and left join to find gaps (missing days)
SELECT d.day, COALESCE(s.total, 0) AS total
FROM generate_series(DATE '2026-01-01', DATE '2026-01-31', INTERVAL '1 day') d(day)
LEFT JOIN daily_sales s ON s.order_date = d.day;
```
**Best practice**: always store timestamps in UTC, convert to `Europe/Amsterdam` only at presentation/BI layer.

