## 11. Transactions & isolation levels
```sql
BEGIN;
UPDATE accounts SET balance = balance - 100 WHERE id = 1;
UPDATE accounts SET balance = balance + 100 WHERE id = 2;
COMMIT;
```
Know the ACID properties and the standard isolation levels: **Read Uncommitted, Read Committed, Repeatable Read, Serializable** — and what anomaly each one prevents (dirty read, non-repeatable read, phantom read). Most warehouses (BigQuery, Snowflake) don't expose classic row-level transactions the way OLTP databases do — worth knowing that distinction for interviews.

