## 14. Suggested learning path
1. Nail joins, window functions, and CTEs cold — these come up in almost every DE technical interview in NL.
2. Practice the dedup / running-total / SCD2 / gaps-and-islands patterns until you can write them without looking them up.
3. Learn to read `EXPLAIN ANALYZE` on Postgres — even if your job uses Snowflake/BigQuery, the reasoning transfers.
4. Pick one cloud warehouse (BigQuery or Snowflake are most common in NL job ads) and learn its JSON/semi-structured functions and cost model (BigQuery bills by bytes scanned — partitioning/clustering directly saves money).
5. Learn dbt: it's the de facto standard SQL transformation tool in the Dutch data engineering market, and it wraps most of section 9 and 13 above into a workflow.
6. Practice on real datasets: StrataScratch, LeetCode SQL, DataLemur — good for interview-style practice of exactly the patterns above.

